nt of Rehabilitation conducting work skills assessments. Rachael worked in a house where four adults lived together, as the house administrator. She worked as a direct support person to help people with disabilities reclaim their lives after living in a state hospital, and with seniors who want to continue to live in their own home.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:group -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\"><!-- wp:heading {\"textColor\":\"black\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"has-black-color has-text-color\"><strong>Marlene McCollum</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-normal-font-size\">Marlene McCollum has worked as a Service Coordinator and now, Case Management Supervisor at regional centers for 19 years. Marlene has worked with infants in the Early Start Program and with adults living in an array of living settings. In addition, she worked as a vocational counselor for an agency where people with disabilities gained work experience in a variety of employment programs. She has also worked with women in crisis who needed safety and support.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"left\",\"id\":28,\"sizeSlug\":\"medium\",\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-medium\"><img src=\"https://choice-powers-change-consulting.local/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Hands-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Picture of hands\" class=\"wp-image-28\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"textColor\":\"black\",\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":17}}} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-black-color has-text-color\" style=\"font-size:17px\"><strong>Choice Powers Change Consulting</strong> is our business-its our passion and how we put our skill set to use. We<br>teach, train, collaborate, and plan with people, to develop and experience reciprocal involvement with their<br>community. We do this through interest-based exploration and personalized supports.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','13-revision-v1','','','2020-10-18 23:40:15','2020-10-18 23:40:15','',13,'https://choice-powers-change-consulting.local/13-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
